## v1.6.0.042226
- Added per-pad stereo pan control in the Sample Pad Mixer, placed above mute/solo, with real-time audio routing updates.
- Added center-detent behavior for pan controls so near-center values snap cleanly to exact center.
- Added pan persistence in sample pad layouts/autosave (`panPercent`) and restore/reset handling.
- Updated mixer layout/sizing calculations after pan-row addition to prevent mute/solo controls from being clipped in dense/small window sizes.
- Upgraded output strip metering to stereo (independent L/R output meters) while keeping pad strips as single-channel post-fader meters.
- Added engine-level stereo output metering API (`output_meter_levels`) and integrated it through MainWindow/Sample Pads mixer display.
- Added equal-power panning in the sample pad audio engine callback and expanded per-pad mix settings to include pan.
- Added sample-pad master-gain sync to Live/Preview mode faders so sample pad engine loudness tracks current mode volume consistently.
- Improved sample pad clip/profile resolution flow:
	- Centralized record/path/profile clip-window resolution for trigger/preload paths.
	- Improved full-file loop detection for native looping decisions.
- Expanded "Send to Sample Pad" assignment menu to support profile-specific assignment (Default / Profile P1-P4) and preserve profile index in assignment payload.
- Enhanced Edit Jingle profile workflow:
	- Added remove-profile button with proper enable/disable state.
	- Improved waveform playhead anchoring/visibility behavior when not actively playing.
	- Tightened preview start-seek ordering and clip-window enforcement around playback start.

## v1.5.0.042026
- Upgraded sample pad playback from single-owner behavior to polyphonic playback, allowing multiple pads/voices to play at once.
- Added per-pad playback ownership/state tracking so pad play/stop state is independent and accurate under concurrent playback.
- Added Sample Pads stop controls:
	- New per-pad "Stop" button under each pad (enabled only while that pad is active/pending).
	- New "Stop All Playback" button in the Sample Pads window to stop all active sample-pad voices.
- Decoupled sample-pad playback controls from main-window transport semantics while preserving shared mode-bus volume sync (Live bus and Preview bus).
- Added dedicated Sample Pad Mixer window with per-pad volume, mute, solo, and live post-fader metering.
- Added mixer state persistence in sample pad layout files (per-pad volume/mute/solo) and autosave/restore integration.
- Added mixer layout polish and responsive behavior improvements for dense single-row channel strips.
- Added single-instance app enforcement with PID lock, stale-lock cleanup, and "terminate first instance" prompt flow.
- Improved auxiliary window lifecycle behavior:
	- Sample Pads and Mixer close when main window closes.
	- Sample Pads and Mixer top-level/taskbar visibility behavior improved on Windows.
- Added proactive sample-pad stream warmup when opening the Sample Pads window to reduce first-trigger cold-start latency.
- Added background preload when assigning pad jingles and preload-on-layout behavior for assigned pad clips.
- Added non-blocking cache-miss trigger path so long-file first triggers no longer block the UI thread.
- Added long-file streaming path for cache misses, including buffered background decode and ffmpeg-pipe fallback for compressed/non-matching sources without creating large temporary files.
- Added startup prebuffering and larger streaming headroom to reduce first-seconds underrun/glitch artifacts on long compressed sources.
- Added engine logic to avoid duplicate in-flight preload work and to skip expensive full preloads for long compressed files when streaming is preferred.
- Added new Options setting "Pad Stream Min" (seconds), persisted as `options/samplePadStreamingMinSeconds`, to control when cache-miss playback uses streaming.

## v1.4.0.041926
- Replaced QMediaPlayer-based sample pad audio with a new custom `SamplePadAudioEngine` backed by PortAudio (`sounddevice`) and `soundfile`/`numpy`.
- Sample pad audio now uses a continuously open PortAudio stream, eliminating pipeline teardown clicks/pops on retrigger.
- Added PCM-level 2ms linear crossfade on retrigger for click-free rapid re-triggering.
- Added PCM decode cache with background `preload()` so audio files are decoded once and reused, eliminating per-trigger I/O latency.
- Stream opens with `latency="low"` and a configurable blocksize (default 128 frames) for reduced trigger-to-audio latency.
- Added "Pad Blocksize" setting to the Options dialog (choices: 64–1024 frames) persisted across sessions.
- Preview mode sample pads now also route through the new engine (previously only Live mode did, leaving Preview mode with the old pop behavior).
- Added `modeChanged` signal to `SamplePadsWindow`; main window now eagerly opens/warms the audio stream for the target device when Live/Preview mode is toggled, preventing a silent first trigger after a mode switch.
- New dependencies: `sounddevice>=0.4,<1`, `soundfile>=0.12,<1`, `numpy>=1.26,<3` (added to `requirements.txt` and `JingleAllTheDay.spec` hidden imports).

## v1.3.0.041926
- Added Sample Pads window with up to 5 boards x 20 pads, pad modes (One Shot, Loop, Release), and per-pad assignment from the jingle list context menu.
- Added board pills and board switching hotkeys (Shift+1-5 by default, optional Ctrl+Shift+1-5), including persistence of the active board.
- Added local and global sample pad triggering (1-0 and Ctrl+1-0), with optional Alt modifier and Windows-native/pynput global hotkey backends.
- Added sample pad layout save/load support, autosave, and startup restore behavior.
- Optimized sample pad autosave so writes only happen when state actually changes, with autosave triggers on board changes, sample window close/hide, and main app exit.
- Fixed autosave recursion during board switching by adding re-entrancy guards around autosave writes.
- Improved looping behavior to reduce clicks/pops:
	- Native seamless looping for untrimmed full-file loops in sample pads, main window, and Edit Jingle dialog.
	- Safer muted-seek handling for manual (trimmed) loop restarts.
	- Improved Release mode stop behavior during rapid press/release interactions.
- Added multi-profile clip offsets per jingle in Edit Jingle:
	- 1 default profile with ability to add up to 4 profile pills.
	- Each profile stores independent start/stop offsets and persists to the library database.
	- Active profile selection is auto-persisted immediately when switching profiles.
- Updated Send to Sample Pad to use the currently active saved clip profile and carry those offsets into pad assignments.
- Persisted clip profile metadata in sample pad layouts so profile-based pad assignments survive layout save/load and autosave.
- Added `pynput` as an optional dependency for global hotkey support.

## v1.2.1.041226
- Added Waveform Cache which stores generated waveform previews on disk to speed up loading and reduce CPU usage.
- Added "Calculate Waveform Previews" action to the Tools menu which generates waveform previews for all jingles in the library that don't already have a persisted waveform preview.
- Added "Auto Generate Waveforms for New Files" option to the Tools menu which, when enabled, automatically generates and persists a waveform preview for any new jingle added to the library.

## v1.1.2.041226
- Added Edit Jingle feature to the context menu of the jingle list.
- Added Edit Jingle dialog window which allows users to edit the start and stop locations of a jingle, as well as preview the jingle including looping behavior.

